      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CAPTAINS KNOCK (9) chases a clean sweep of the Carnival of Cups series and a $1million bonus. Has been dominant in winning the previous four rounds, the most recent coming from a similar barrier at Albury two back. Drew very wide when beating only one home in a Miracle Mile qualifier since but will relish the step up in trip having won his two previous attempts at the distance. UBETCHA TIGERPIE (11) performed well through the Menangle carnival, highlighted by a 2.3m fourth in a Miracle Mile qualifier. Had gone into that with seconds in three of his previous four Menangle starts behind the likes of Swayzee and Rakero Rocket. Untried at the distance but the form is good enough to see him make a race of it. Former WA pacer MAGNUS VICTOR (8) will strip fitter having finished midfield when resuming at Menangle last week. Goes well at this distance so can improve. MAX DELIGHT (10) was a 4.6m fourth in a G2 at Menangle last week and won his only try at this circuit and distance.",
